name: Deluge
description:
Deluge
Gouache on paper
2011
A3
FRAMED

This particular piece was inspired by the flooding here in South East Queensland back in January 2011. The whole summer season was pretty wet and miserable, filled with endless rainy days. There were flash floods which came as such a shock to everybody because they were in areas previously considered to be safe from flooding, one little township was swept away. Then a bit later in the season, North Queensland was hit by a category 5 cyclone, Yasi.

The experience that year was very moving. I wanted to convey the tumultuous feelings it left me with. Awe of the power of nature and horror at the same time. 

Framed in a premium hefty black wooden frame. Looks great on the wall, I gotta tell ya!

name: Zebrafinches
description:
Zebra Finches
A3
Acrylic, Gouache & Pencil On Paper.
UNFRAMED
paper is slightly rippled and buckled from layers and layers of paint and pencil and so much love! Adds a bit of character if you ask me;-)

Spectacular detail! So much time has gone into this piece. Although toadstools aren't really related to finches in any natural sense, the colours and the patterns looked similar from a design point of view.

I learnt a little about the history of the toadstool while researching images. Apparently they were used by Siberian shamans. First they would eat a few of the mushrooms which would somehow enhance its hallucinogenic properties then urinate, giving this to somebody else to drink... Honestly, who thinks of doing that!?
